==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Opinionative
<hw>O*pin"ion*a*tive</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Unduly
attached to one's own opinions; opinionated.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of the nature of an opinion; conjectured.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Things both <xex>opinionative</xex> and
practical.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Bunyan.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>O*pin"ion*a*tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>O*pin"ion*a*tive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opinionator</ent>⟦br⟧
